class.designerProperty: Key: AcceptCookies, DisplayName: AcceptCookies, FieldType: Boolean, DefaultValue: True, Description: Gets or sets whether the application's WebkitWebView instances send and accept cookies. WebkitCookieManager library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: AcceptFileSchemeCookies, DisplayName: AcceptFileSchemeCookies, FieldType: Boolean, DefaultValue: False, Description: This method was deprecated in API level 30. This setting is not secure. WebkitCookieManager library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: AcceptThirdPartyCookies, DisplayName: AcceptThirdPartyCookies, FieldType: Boolean, DefaultValue: False, Description: Gets or sets whether the WebkitWebView should allow third party cookies to be set. WebkitCookieManager library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: AllowContentAccess, DisplayName: AllowContentAccess, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Enables or disables content URL access within WebkitWebView. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: AllowFileAccess, DisplayName: AllowFileAccess, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Enables or disables file access within WebkitWebView. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: AllowFullScreenVideo, DisplayName: AllowFullScreenVideo, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: NOT_ALLOWED, List: NOT_ALLOWED|ALLOWED|ALLOWED_FORCE_LANDSCAPE, Description: This method enables or disables WebkitWebView's ability to play online video in full screen. ALLOWED_FORCE_LANDSCAPE - Force full screen video to play in landscape screen orientation.WebkitWebChromeClient library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect. IMPORTANT SoftOrientation library is required or other mathods which will prevent the Activity to redraw on the orientation change. SoftOrientation Url https://www.b4x.com/android/forum/threads/softorientation-library-for-activitiy-and-b4xpages-based-projects.143896/#post-912287

Key: AppCacheEnabled, DisplayName: AppCacheEnabled, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: This method was deprecated in API level 30. The Application Cache API is deprecated and this method will become a no-op on all Android versions once support is removed in Chromium. Consider using Service Workers instead. See https://web.dev/appcache-removal/ for more information. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: AppCacheMaxSize, DisplayName: AppCacheMaxSize, FieldType: Int, DefaultValue: 0, MinRange: 0, Description: Value in bytes. Value can not be negative. 0-default. This method was deprecated in API level 18. Quota is managed automatically; this method is a no-op. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: AllowFileAccessFromFileURLs, DisplayName: AllowFileAccessFromFileURLs, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: This method was deprecated in API level 30. This setting is not secure. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: AllowUniversalAccessFromFileURLs, DisplayName: AllowUniversalAccessFromFileURLs, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: This method was deprecated in API level 30. This setting is not secure. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: AppCachePath, DisplayName: AppCachePath, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: , Description: This method was deprecated in API level 30. The Application Cache API is deprecated and this method will become a no-op on all Android versions once support is removed in Chromium. Consider using Service Workers instead. See https://web.dev/appcache-removal/ for more information. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: BlockNetworkImage, DisplayName: BlockNetworkImage, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether the WebView should not load image resources from the network (resources accessed via http and https URI schemes). WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: BlockNetworkLoads, DisplayName: BlockNetworkLoads, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether the WebView should not load resources from the network. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: BuiltInZoomControls, DisplayName: BuiltInZoomControls, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether the WebView should use its built-in zoom mechanisms. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: CacheMode, DisplayName: CacheMode, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: CACHEMODE_LOAD_DEFAULT, List: CACHEMODE_LOAD_DEFAULT|CACHEMODE_LOAD_CACHE_ELSE_NETWORK|CACHEMODE_LOAD_NO_CACHE|CACHEMODE_LOAD_CACHE_ONLY, Description: Overrides the way the cache is used. Values: CACHEMODE_LOAD_DEFAULT or CACHEMODE_LOAD_CACHE_ELSE_NETWORK or CACHEMODE_LOAD_NO_CACHE or CACHEMODE_LOAD_CACHE_ONLY. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: CursiveFontFamily, DisplayName: CursiveFontFamily, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: , Description: Sets the cursive font family name. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: DatabaseEnabled, DisplayName: DatabaseEnabled, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether the database storage API is enabled. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: DatabasePath, DisplayName: DatabasePath, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: , Description: This method was deprecated in API level 19. Database paths are managed by the implementation and calling this method will have no effect. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: DefaultFixedFontSize, DisplayName: DefaultFixedFontSize, FieldType: Int, DefaultValue: 0, MinRange: 0, Description: Sets the default fixed font size. 0-Default. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: DefaultFontSize, DisplayName: DefaultFontSize, FieldType: Int, DefaultValue: 0, MinRange: 0, Description: Sets the default font size. 0-Default. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: DefaultTextEncodingName, DisplayName: DefaultTextEncodingName, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: , Description: Sets the default text encoding name to use when decoding html pages. The default is "UTF-8". WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: DisabledActionModeMenuItems, DisplayName: DisabledActionModeMenuItems, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: MENU_ITEM_NONE, List: MENU_ITEM_NONE|MENU_ITEM_PROCESS_TEXT|MENU_ITEM_SHARE|MENU_ITEM_WEB_SEARCH, Description: Disables the action mode menu items according to menuItems flag. Values: MENU_ITEM_NONE or MENU_ITEM_SHARE or MENU_ITEM_WEB_SEARCH or MENU_ITEM_PROCESS_TEXT. Default value is MENU_ITEM_NONE. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: DisplayZoomControls, DisplayName: DisplayZoomControls, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether the WebkitWebView should display on-screen zoom controls when using the built-in zoom mechanisms. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: DomStorageEnabled, DisplayName: DomStorageEnabled, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether the DOM storage API is enabled. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: EnableSlowWholeDocumentDraw, DisplayName: EnableSlowWholeDocumentDraw, FieldType: Boolean, DefaultValue: False, Description: For apps targeting the L release WebView has a new default behavior that reduces memory footprint and increases performance by intelligently choosing the portion of the HTML document that needs to be drawn.

Key: EnableSmoothTransition, DisplayName: EnableSmoothTransition, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: This method was deprecated in API level 17. This method is now obsolete, and will become a no-op in future. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: FantasyFontFamily, DisplayName: FantasyFontFamily, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: , Description: Sets the fantasy font family name. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: FixedFontFamily, DisplayName: FixedFontFamily, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: , Description: Sets the fixed font family name. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: ForceDark, DisplayName: ForceDark, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: FORCE_DARK_AUTO, List: FORCE_DARK_AUTO|FORCE_DARK_OFF|FORCE_DARK_ON, Description: Set the force dark mode for this WebkitWebView. Values: FORCE_DARK_OFF or FORCE_DARK_AUTO or FORCE_DARK_ON. Default value is FORCE_DARK_AUTO. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: GeolocationDatabasePath, DisplayName: GeolocationDatabasePath, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: , Description: This method was deprecated in API level 24. Geolocation database are managed by the implementation and calling this method will have no effect. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: GeolocationEnabled, DisplayName: GeolocationEnabled, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether Geolocation is enabled. Permissions in manifest: Manifest.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION and Manifest.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: HorizontalFadingEdgeEnabled, DisplayName: HorizontalFadingEdgeEnabled, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Define whether the horizontal edges should be faded when this view is scrolled horizontally. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: HorizontalScrollBarEnabled, DisplayName: HorizontalScrollBarEnabled, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Define whether the horizontal scrollbar should be drawn or not. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: HorizontalScrollbarThumbColor, DisplayName: HorizontalScrollBarThumbColor, FieldType: Color, DefaultValue: Null, Description: Defines the horizontal thumb color. Works on Api 29 and above. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: HorizontalScrollbarTrackColor, DisplayName: HorizontalScrollBarTrackColor, FieldType: Color, DefaultValue: Null, Description: Defines the horizontal track color. Works on Api 29 and above. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.
Key: InitialScale, DisplayName: InitialScale, FieldType: Int, DefaultValue: 0, MinRange: 0, MaxRange: 1000, Description: Sets the initial scale in percent for this WebkitWebView. 0 means default.

Key: JavaScriptCanOpenWindowsAutomatically, DisplayName: JavaScriptCanOpenWindowsAutomatically, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Allow JavaScript to open windows automatically. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.
Key: JavaScriptEnabled, DisplayName: JavaScriptEnabled, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Tells the WebkitWebView to enable JavaScript execution.

Key: LightTouchEnabled, DisplayName: LightTouchEnabled, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: This method was deprecated in API level 18. From Build.VERSION_CODES.JELLY_BEAN this setting is obsolete and has no effect. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: LoadWithOverviewMode, DisplayName: LoadWithOverviewMode, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether the WebkitWebView loads pages in overview mode, that is, zooms out the content to fit on screen by width. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: LoadsImagesAutomatically, DisplayName: LoadsImagesAutomatically, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether the WebkitWebView should load image resources. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: MediaPlaybackRequiresUserGesture, DisplayName: MediaPlaybackRequiresUserGesture, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether the WebkitWebView requires a user gesture to play media. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: MinimumFontSize, DisplayName: MinimumFontSize, FieldType: Int, DefaultValue: 0, MinRange: 0, Description: Sets the minimum font size. 0-Default. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: MinimumLogicalFontSize, DisplayName: MinimumLogicalFontSize, FieldType: Int, DefaultValue: 0, MinRange: 0, Description: Sets the minimum logical font size. 0-Default. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: MixedContentMode, DisplayName: MixedContentMode, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: MIXED_CONTENT_DEFAULT, List: MIXED_CONTENT_DEFAULT|MIXED_CONTENT_ALWAYS_ALLOW|MIXED_CONTENT_COMPATIBILITY_MODE|MIXED_CONTENT_NEVER_ALLOW, Description: Configures the WebkitWebView's behavior when a secure origin attempts to load a resource from an insecure origin. Values: MIXED_CONTENT_ALWAYS_ALLOW or MIXED_CONTENT_NEVER_ALLOW or MIXED_CONTENT_COMPATIBILITY_MODE. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: NeedInitialFocus, DisplayName: NeedInitialFocus, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Tells the WebkitWebView whether it needs to set a node to have focus when WebView#requestFocus is called. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: OffscreenPreRaster, DisplayName: OffscreenPreRaster, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether this WebkitWebView should raster tiles when it is offscreen but attached to a window. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.
Key: RequestFocus, DisplayName: RequestFocus, FieldType: Boolean, DefaultValue: False, Description: Call this to try to give focus to WebkitWebView at application start.

Key: SafeBrowsingEnabled, DisplayName: SafeBrowsingEnabled, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether Safe Browsing is enabled. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: SansSerifFontFamily, DisplayName: SansSerifFontFamily, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: , Description: Sets the sans-serif font family name. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: SaveFormData, DisplayName: SaveFormData, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: This method was deprecated in API level 26. In Android O and afterwards, this function does not have any effect, the form data will be saved to platform's autofill service if applicable. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: SavePassword, DisplayName: SavePassword, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: This method was deprecated in API level 18. Saving passwords in WebView will not be supported in future versions. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: ScrollbarFadingEnabled, DisplayName: ScrollBarFadingEnabled, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Define whether scrollbars will fade when the view is not scrolling. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: ScrollBarDefaultDelayBeforeFade, DisplayName: ScrollBarDefaultDelayBeforeFade, FieldType: Int, DefaultValue: 0, MinRange: 0, Description: Define the delay in milliseconds before scrollbars fade. 0-Default. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: ScrollBarFadeDuration, DisplayName: ScrollBarFadeDuration, FieldType: Int, DefaultValue: 0, Description: Define the scrollbar fade duration in milliseconds. 0-Default. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: ScrollBarSize, DisplayName: ScrollBarSize, FieldType: Int, DefaultValue: 0, MinRange: 0, Description: Define the scrollbar size in dip. 0-Default. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: ScrollBarStyle, DisplayName: ScrollBarStyle, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT_STYLE, List: DEFAULT_STYLE|SCROLLBARS_INSIDE_OVERLAY|SCROLLBARS_INSIDE_INSET|SCROLLBARS_OUTSIDE_OVERLAY|SCROLLBARS_OUTSIDE_INSET, Description: Specify the style of the scrollbars. The scrollbars can be overlaid or inset. When inset they add to the padding of the view. And the scrollbars can be drawn inside the padding area or on the edge of the view. For example if a view has a background drawable and you want to draw the scrollbars inside the padding specified by the drawable you can use SCROLLBARS_INSIDE_OVERLAY or SCROLLBARS_INSIDE_INSET. If you want them to appear at the edge of the view ignoring the padding then you can use SCROLLBARS_OUTSIDE_OVERLAY or SCROLLBARS_OUTSIDE_INSET. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: SerifFontFamily, DisplayName: SerifFontFamily, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: , Description: Sets the serif font family name. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: SetDownloadListener, DisplayName: SetDownloadListenerEnabled, FieldType: Boolean, DefaultValue: False, Description: Set and start Download Listener. Events: FileDownloadInitialized (DownloadProperties1 as DownloadProperties). Use StartFileDownload method to download file with native Download Manager or use your own method. WebkitDownloadListener library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: SetWebChromeClient, DisplayName: SetWebChromeClientEnabled, FieldType: Boolean, DefaultValue: False, Description: Sets the chrome handler. This is an implementation of WebChromeClient for use in handling JavaScript dialogs favicons titles and the progress. Library will initialize WebChromeClient by itself and associate it with WebkitWebView. Online file upload option will be enabled by default. Geolocation permission will be handled like any other permission request and will trigger PermissionRequest event. WebkitWebChromeClient library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: SetWebViewClient, DisplayName: SetWebViewClientEnabled, FieldType: Boolean, DefaultValue: False, Description: Sets the WebViewClient that will receive various notifications and requests. Library will initialize WebViewCliect by itself and associate it with WebkitWebView. WebkitWebViewClient library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: StandardFontFamily, DisplayName: StandardFontFamily, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: , Description: Sets the standard font family name. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: SupportMultipleWindows, DisplayName: SupportMultipleWindows, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether the WebkitWebView whether supports multiple windows. WebkitWebViewSettings and WebkitWebChromeClient library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: SupportZoom, DisplayName: SupportZoom, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether the WebkitWebView should support zooming using its on-screen zoom controls and gestures. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: SwipeToReload, DisplayName: SwipeToReload, FieldType: Boolean, DefaultValue: False, Description: Enable WebkitWebView's Swipe to Reload function. WebkitWebViewClient library required and JavasctriptEnabled = True, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: TextZoom, DisplayName: TextZoom, FieldType: Int, DefaultValue: 0, MinRange: 0, Description: Sets the text zoom of the page in percent. 0-Default. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: UseWideViewPort, DisplayName: UseWideViewPort, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Sets whether the WebkitWebView should enable support for the "viewport" HTML meta tag or should use a wide viewport. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: UserAgentString, DisplayName: UserAgentString, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: , Description: Sets the WebkitWebView's user-agent string. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: VerticalFadingEdgeEnabled, DisplayName: VerticalFadingEdgeEnabled, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Define whether the vertical edges should be faded when this view is scrolled vertically. False - Default. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: VerticalScrollBarEnabled, DisplayName: VerticalScrollBarEnabled, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: DEFAULT, List: DEFAULT|TRUE|FALSE, Description: Define whether the vertical scrollbar should be drawn or not. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: VerticalScrollbarPosition, DisplayName: VerticalScrollBarPosition, FieldType: String, DefaultValue: SCROLLBAR_POSITION_DEFAULT, List: SCROLLBAR_POSITION_DEFAULT|SCROLLBAR_POSITION_LEFT|SCROLLBAR_POSITION_RIGHT, Description: Set the position of the vertical scroll bar. Should be one of SCROLLBAR_POSITION_DEFAULT or SCROLLBAR_POSITION_LEFT or SCROLLBAR_POSITION_RIGHT. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: VerticalScrollbarThumbColor, DisplayName: VerticalScrollBarThumbColor, FieldType: Color, DefaultValue: Null, Description: Defines the vertical scrollbar thumb color. Works on Api 29 and above. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

Key: VerticalScrollbarTrackColor, DisplayName: VerticalScrollBarTrackColor, FieldType: Color, DefaultValue: Null, Description: Defines the vertical scrollbar track color. Works on Api 29 and above. WebkitWebViewSettings library required, otherwise the setting will have no effect.

method.name: IsInitialized
method.comment: Tests whether the object has been initialized.

method.name: _addjavascriptinterface
method.comment: Injects the supplied JavascriptInterface As Object into this WebkitWebView. The object is injected into all frames of the web page, including all the iframes, using the supplied name. This allows the Java object's methods to be accessed from JavaScript. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _cangoback
method.comment: Gets whether this WebkitWebView has a back history item. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _cangobackorforward
method.comment: Gets whether the page can go back or forward the given number of steps. Steps as Int (negative - back or positive - forward number of steps to move the history). Added in API level 1.

method.name: _cangoforward
method.comment: Gets whether this WebkitWebView has a forward history item. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _capturescreenshottobitmap
method.comment: Capture WebkitWebView visible area to Bitmap.

method.name: _capturescreenshottoimagefile
method.comment: Capture WebkitWebView visible area to Image File. Permission WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE required on API level 29 and above. ImageType: "jpeg" or "png" or "webp" ImageQuality: 1 to 100 For API level below 29 you must first request WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE permission. For API level 29 and above, you must save the file to a Shared Folder (FileProvider).

method.name: _clearcache
method.comment: Clears the resource cache. Note that the cache is per-application, so this will clear the cache for all WebkitWebViews used. IncludeDiskFiles As Boolean (if false, only the RAM cache is cleared) Added in API level 1.

method.name: _clearfocus
method.comment: Called when this WebkitWebView wants to give up focus. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _clearformdata
method.comment: Removes the autocomplete popup from the currently focused form field, if present. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _clearhistory
method.comment: Tells this WebkitWebView to clear its internal back/forward list. Added in API level 1

method.name: _clearmatches
method.comment: Clears the highlighting surrounding text matches created by findAllAsync(String). Added in API level 3.

method.name: _clearsslpreferences
method.comment: Clears the SSL preferences table stored in response to proceeding with SSL certificate errors. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _computescroll
method.comment: Called by a parent to request that a child update its values for mScrollX and mScrollY if necessary. Added in API level 1

method.name: _enableslowwholedocumentdraw
method.comment: For apps targeting the L release, WebkitWebView has a new default behavior that reduces memory footprint and increases performance by intelligently choosing the portion of the HTML document that needs to be drawn. These optimizations are transparent to the developers. Added in API level 21

method.name: _executejavascript
method.comment: Execute Javascript in WebkitWebView. Important: WebkitWebView1.JavaScriptEnabled=True 'Must be set to True somewhere in code Added in API level 19.

method.name: _executejavascript2
method.comment: Execute Javascript in WebkitWebView and got asynchronius backward Result. Event "ExecuteJavaScriptResult (Result as String)" will be fired when result is available. Result can be "null". Important: WebkitWebView1.JavaScriptEnabled=True 'Must be set to True somewhere in code Added in API level 19 Example: WebkitWebView1.Settings.JavaScriptEnabled=True 'Must be set to True somewhere in code WebkitWebView1.ExecuteJavascript2([Your JavaScript Code]) Wait For WebkitWebView1_ExecuteJavaScriptResult (Result As String) 'Do your stuff with Result

method.name: _findallasync
method.comment: Finds all instances of find on the page and highlights them, asynchronously. Added in API level 16.

method.name: _findfocus
method.comment: Find the view in the hierarchy rooted at this view that currently has focus. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _findnext
method.comment: Highlights and scrolls to the next match found by FindAllAsync(Find As String), wrapping around page boundaries as necessary. Added in API level 3.

method.name: _flingscroll
method.comment: Added in API level 1.

method.name: _getaccessibilityclassname
method.comment: Return the class name of this object to be used for accessibility purposes. Added in API level 23.

method.name: _getcontentheight
method.comment: Gets the height in pixels of the HTML content. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _getcookiemanager
method.comment: Gets WebkitCookieManager's properties and methods. WebkitCookieManager library required. Class is auto initialized.

method.name: _getcopybackforwardlist
method.comment: Gets the WebBackForwardList for this WebkitWebView. This contains the back/forward list for use in querying each item in the history stack. This is a copy of the private WebBackForwardList so it contains only a snapshot of the current state. Multiple calls to this method may return different objects. The object returned from this method will not be updated to reflect any new state. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _getdownloadlistener
method.comment: Gets WebkitDownloadListener's properties and methods. WebkitDownloadListener library required. Class is auto initialized.

method.name: _getfavicon
method.comment: Gets the favicon for the current page. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _getisprivatebrowsingenabled
method.comment: Gets whether private browsing is enabled in this WebkitWebView. Added in API level 11.

method.name: _getmimetypemap
method.comment: Gets WebkitMimeTypeMap's properties and methods. WebkitMimeTypeMap library required. Class is auto initialized.

method.name: _getoncheckistexteditor
method.comment: Check whether the called view is a text editor, in which case it would make sense to automatically display a soft input window for it. Added in API level 3.

method.name: _getoriginalurl
method.comment: Gets the original URL for the current page. Added in API level 3.

method.name: _getprogress
method.comment: Gets the progress for the current page. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _getsafebrowsingprivacypolicyurl
method.comment: Returns a URL pointing to the privacy policy for Safe Browsing reporting. Gets android.net.Uri as AndroidNetUri. Link for AndroidNetUri library and documentations: https://www.b4x.com/android/forum/threads/androidneturi-library.136402/ Added in API level 27.

method.name: _getsettings
method.comment: Gets WebkitWebViewSettings properties and methods. WebkitWebViewSettings library required. Class is auto initialized.

method.name: _gettitle
method.comment: Gets the title for the current page. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _geturl
method.comment: Gets the URL for the current page. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _geturlutil
method.comment: Gets WebkitURLUtil's properties and methods. WebkitURLUtil library required. Class is auto initialized.

method.name: _getview
method.comment: Get WebkitWebView as android.view.View.

method.name: _getwebview
method.comment: Gets native B4A WebView which is auto associated with WebkitWebView.

method.name: _getwebviewdatabase
method.comment: Gets WebkitWebViewDatabase's properties and methods. WebkitWebViewDatabase library required. Class is auto initialized.

method.name: _goback
method.comment: Goes back in the history of this WebkitWebView. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _gobackorforward
method.comment: Goes to the history item that is the number of steps away from the current item. Steps is negative if backward and positive if forward. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _goforward
method.comment: Goes forward in the history of this WebkitWebView. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _initialize
method.comment: Method is called automatically when object is added through Designer.

method.name: _invokezoompicker
method.comment: Invokes the graphical zoom picker widget for this WebkitWebView. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _isfocused
method.comment: Returns true if this view has focus. Added in API level 26.

method.name: _loaddata
method.comment: Note that JavaScript's same origin policy means that script running in a page loaded using this method will be unable to access content loaded using any scheme other than 'data', including 'http(s)'. To avoid this restriction, use LoadDataWithBaseURL() with an appropriate base URL. The encoding parameter specifies whether the data Is base64 Or URL encoded. If the data Is base64 encoded, the value of the encoding parameter must be "base64". Added in API level 1.

method.name: _loaddatawithbaseurl
method.comment: Loads the given data into this WebkitWebView, using baseUrl as the base URL for the content. The base URL is used both to resolve relative URLs and when applying JavaScript's same origin policy. The historyUrl is used for the history entry. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _loadfilefromdirassets
method.comment: Loads file (HTML, TXT, PNG, JPG...) from DirAssets folder into WebkitWebView. FileName As String - Name of file or file path and name (Example: "test.html" or "TestFolder/test.html"). IncludeSubFolders As Boolean - True for an html file whose objects are in a subfolder or multiple subfolders. False for an html file that has no additional objects in the subfolders but only at the root of the Asset folder. For a non html files value is not important (True or False). Added in API level 1.

method.name: _loadhtmlstring
method.comment: Use this method to load HTML string into WebkitWebView. Works on API level 1 and above.

method.name: _loadurl
method.comment: Loads the given URL. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _loadurl2
method.comment: Loads the given URL with additional HTTP headers, specified as a map from name to value. Note that if this map contains any of the headers that are set by default by this WebkitWebView, such as those controlling caching, accept types or the User-Agent, their values may be overridden by this WebkitWebView's defaults. Added in API level 8

method.name: _pagedown
method.comment: Scrolls the contents of this WebkitWebView down by half the page size. ToBottom As Boolean (true to jump to bottom of page). Added in API level 1.

method.name: _pageup
method.comment: Scrolls the contents of this WebkitWebView up by half the view size. ToTop As Boolean (true to jump to the top of the page). Added in API level 1.

method.name: _pause
method.comment: Does a best-effort attempt to pause any processing that can be paused safely, such as animations and geolocation. Note that this call does not pause JavaScript. To pause JavaScript globally, use pauseTimers(). Added in API level 11

method.name: _pausetimers
method.comment: Pauses all layout, parsing, and JavaScript timers for all WebkitWebViews. This is a global requests, not restricted to just this WebkitWebView. This can be useful if the application has been paused. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _posturl
method.comment: Loads the URL with postData using "POST" method into this WebView. Added in API level 5.

method.name: _printcontent
method.comment: This method is used to print WebkitWebView content.

method.name: _reload
method.comment: Reloads the current URL. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _removejavascriptinterface
method.comment: Removes a previously injected Java object from this WebkitWebView. Note that the removal will not be reflected in JavaScript until the page is next (re)loaded. Added in API level 11

method.name: _removeview
method.comment: Use this method to remove this view from parent.

method.name: _requestfocus
method.comment: Call this to try to give focus to WebkitWebView. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _resume
method.comment: Resumes a WebkitWebView after a previous call to Pause. Added in API level 11.

method.name: _resumetimers
method.comment: Resumes all layout, parsing, and JavaScript timers for all WebkitWebViews. This will resume dispatching all timers. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _savewebarchive
method.comment: Saves the current view as a web archive. Filename As String (the filename where the archive should be placed This value cannot be null). Added in API level 11

method.name: _setbackgroundcolor
method.comment: Sets the background color for this view. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _setdatadirectorysuffix
method.comment: Define the directory used to store WebView data for the current process. Added in API level 28.

method.name: _setinitialscale
method.comment: Sets the initial scale in percent for this WebkitWebView. 0 means default. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _setjavascriptenabled
method.comment: Tells the WebkitWebView to enable JavaScript execution. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _setlayout
method.comment: Changes the WebkitWebView's position and size.

method.name: _setlayoutanimated
method.comment: Changes the WebkitWebView's position and size with animation. Duration As Int - Duration of the animation in milliseconds

method.name: _setnetworkavailable
method.comment: Informs WebView of the network state. Added in API level 3.

method.name: _setoverscrollmode
method.comment: Set the over-scroll mode for this view. Values: OVER_SCROLL_ALWAYS, OVER_SCROLL_IF_CONTENT_SCROLLS (allow over-scrolling only if the view content is larger than the container), or OVER_SCROLL_NEVER. Setting the over-scroll mode of a view will have an effect only if the view is capable of scrolling. Added in API level 9

method.name: _setrendererprioritypolicy
method.comment: Set the renderer priority policy for this WebkitWebView. Added in API level 26

method.name: _setswipetoreload
method.comment: Enable or disable WebkitWebView's Swipe to Reload function. WebkitWebViewClient required and JavaScriptEnabled must be set to True.

method.name: _stoploading
method.comment: Stops the current load. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _swipetoreloadrefreshanimation
method.comment: This method renders the rotating circle used for SwipeToReload. This method does not initiate a page refresh but only a visual animation. WebkitWebViewClient required and JavaScriptEnabled must be set to True.

method.name: _zoomby
method.comment: Performs a zoom operation in this WebkitWebView. ZoomFactor As Float (the zoom factor to apply. The zoom factor will be clamped to the WebkitWebView's zoom limits. This value must be in the range 0.01 to 100.0 inclusive). Added in API level 21

method.name: _zoomin
method.comment: Performs zoom in in this WebkitWebView. Added in API level 1.

method.name: _zoomout
method.comment: Performs zoom out in this WebkitWebView. Added in API level 1.

property.name: _accessibilityclassname
property.comment: Return the class name of this object to be used for accessibility purposes. Added in API level 23.

property.name: _contentheight
property.comment: Gets the height in pixels of the HTML content. Added in API level 1.

property.name: _cookiemanager
property.comment: Gets WebkitCookieManager's properties and methods. WebkitCookieManager library required. Class is auto initialized.

property.name: _copybackforwardlist
property.comment: Gets the WebBackForwardList for this WebkitWebView. This contains the back/forward list for use in querying each item in the history stack. This is a copy of the private WebBackForwardList so it contains only a snapshot of the current state. Multiple calls to this method may return different objects. The object returned from this method will not be updated to reflect any new state. Added in API level 1.

property.name: _downloadlistener
property.comment: Gets WebkitDownloadListener's properties and methods. WebkitDownloadListener library required. Class is auto initialized.

property.name: _favicon
property.comment: Gets the favicon for the current page. Added in API level 1.

property.name: _isprivatebrowsingenabled
property.comment: Gets whether private browsing is enabled in this WebkitWebView. Added in API level 11.

property.name: _javascriptenabled
property.comment: Tells the WebkitWebView to enable JavaScript execution. Added in API level 1.

property.name: _mimetypemap
property.comment: Gets WebkitMimeTypeMap's properties and methods. WebkitMimeTypeMap library required. Class is auto initialized.

property.name: _oncheckistexteditor
property.comment: Check whether the called view is a text editor, in which case it would make sense to automatically display a soft input window for it. Added in API level 3.

property.name: _originalurl
property.comment: Gets the original URL for the current page. Added in API level 3.

property.name: _progress
property.comment: Gets the progress for the current page. Added in API level 1.

property.name: _safebrowsingprivacypolicyurl
property.comment: Returns a URL pointing to the privacy policy for Safe Browsing reporting. Gets android.net.Uri as AndroidNetUri. Link for AndroidNetUri library and documentations: https://www.b4x.com/android/forum/threads/androidneturi-library.136402/ Added in API level 27.

property.name: _settings
property.comment: Gets WebkitWebViewSettings properties and methods. WebkitWebViewSettings library required. Class is auto initialized.

property.name: _swipetoreload
property.comment: Enable or disable WebkitWebView's Swipe to Reload function. WebkitWebViewClient required and JavaScriptEnabled must be set to True.

property.name: _title
property.comment: Gets the title for the current page. Added in API level 1.

property.name: _url
property.comment: Gets the URL for the current page. Added in API level 1.

property.name: _urlutil
property.comment: Gets WebkitURLUtil's properties and methods. WebkitURLUtil library required. Class is auto initialized.

property.name: _view
property.comment: Get WebkitWebView as android.view.View.

property.name: _webview
property.comment: Gets native B4A WebView which is auto associated with WebkitWebView.

property.name: _webviewdatabase
property.comment: Gets WebkitWebViewDatabase's properties and methods. WebkitWebViewDatabase library required. Class is auto initialized.

property.name: _backgroundcolor
property.comment: Sets the background color for this view. Added in API level 1.

property.name: _datadirectorysuffix
property.comment: Define the directory used to store WebView data for the current process. Added in API level 28.

property.name: _initialscale
property.comment: Sets the initial scale in percent for this WebkitWebView. 0 means default. Added in API level 1.

property.name: _networkavailable
property.comment: Informs WebView of the network state. Added in API level 3.

property.name: _overscrollmode
property.comment: Set the over-scroll mode for this view. Values: OVER_SCROLL_ALWAYS, OVER_SCROLL_IF_CONTENT_SCROLLS (allow over-scrolling only if the view content is larger than the container), or OVER_SCROLL_NEVER. Setting the over-scroll mode of a view will have an effect only if the view is capable of scrolling. Added in API level 9

method.name: IsInitialized
method.comment: Tests whether the object has been initialized.

method.name: _initialize
method.comment: Initializes the object.
